<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/1075: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-22T14:00:00+09:00">October 22, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 22—5:24 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>197. The Government yesterday instructed the Japanese Ambassadors in
                            Italy and France to address inquiries to the Governments to which they
                            are respectively accredited, and to express verbally the views which you
                            outlined to Debuchi. I understand that the text of Government’s
                            instructions has been repeated to Debuchi for your information.<note n="52" xml:id="d126fn52">On October 30, the Japanese Ambassador
                                reported to the Department the steps which his Government had taken;
                                memorandum of conversation not printed (500 A15a3/1219).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>